<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bpmn:definitions xmlns:bpmn="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/MODEL" xmlns:bpmndi="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/DI" xmlns:dc="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DC" xmlns:spiffworkflow="http://spiffworkflow.org/bpmn/schema/1.0/core" xmlns:di="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DI" id="Definitions_1" targetNamespace="http://bpmn.io/schema/bpmn" exporter="Camunda Modeler" exporterVersion="3.0.0-dev">
  <bpmn:process id="Process_feature_showcase" isExecutable="true">

    <bpmn:startEvent id="StartEvent_1">
      <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_1</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:startEvent>

    <!-- Script Task: uses code module functions + console output -->
    <bpmn:scriptTask id="Activity_InitOrder" name="Initialize Order" scriptFormat="python">
      <bpmn:incoming>Flow_1</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_2</bpmn:outgoing>
      <bpmn:script>
# ---- Code Module Demo ----
# These functions come from helpers.py (the process model's code module).
# They are automatically available in any script context.

customer_name = "Alice Johnson"

order_items = [
    {"name": "Widget A", "price": 29.99, "qty": 3},
    {"name": "Widget B", "price": 149.50, "qty": 2},
    {"name": "Gadget C", "price": 9.99,  "qty": 5},
]

# ---- Console Output Demo ----
# print() output is captured and streamed to the frontend console panel.
print("=== Order Initialization ===")
print(f"Customer: {customer_name}")

order_total = calculate_order_total(order_items)
print(f"Order total: {format_currency(order_total)}")

priority = get_priority(order_total)
print(f"Priority: {priority}")

created_at = get_current_timestamp()
print(f"Created at: {created_at}")
print("============================")

view_count = 0
      </bpmn:script>
    </bpmn:scriptTask>

    <!-- Manual Task 1: Review Order -->
    <!-- preScript runs once when the task becomes ready -->
    <!-- formLoadScript runs each time the task is fetched/viewed -->
    <bpmn:manualTask id="Activity_ReviewOrder" name="Review Order">
      <bpmn:extensionElements>
        <spiffworkflow:preScript>
# ---- PreScript Demo ----
# Runs once when this task is created. Uses code module function.
print("PreScript: Preparing review for " + customer_name)
formatted_total = format_currency(order_total)
        </spiffworkflow:preScript>
        <spiffworkflow:formLoadScript>
# ---- FormLoadScript Demo ----
# Runs every time this task is fetched/viewed.
# Great for counters, timestamps, or refreshing external data.
view_count = view_count + 1
last_viewed = get_current_timestamp()
print(f"FormLoadScript: Review task viewed {view_count} time(s)")
        </spiffworkflow:formLoadScript>
        <spiffworkflow:instructionsForEndUser>
## Order Review

**Customer:** {{ customer_name }}

| Item | Price | Qty | Subtotal |
|------|-------|-----|----------|
{% for item in order_items %}| {{ item.name }} | ${{ item.price }} | {{ item.qty }} | ${{ "%.2f"|format(item.price * item.qty) }} |
{% endfor %}

**Order Total:** {{ formatted_total }}
**Priority:** {{ priority }}
**Created:** {{ created_at }}

---
*This task has been viewed {{ view_count }} time(s). Last viewed: {{ last_viewed }}*

*The view count increments because of the **formLoadScript** running on each page load.*

*Click Continue to proceed to the confirmation step, where you can use the **Back** button to return here.*
        </spiffworkflow:instructionsForEndUser>
      </bpmn:extensionElements>
      <bpmn:incoming>Flow_2</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_3</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:manualTask>

    <!-- Manual Task 2: Confirm Submission -->
    <bpmn:manualTask id="Activity_ConfirmSubmission" name="Confirm Submission">
      <bpmn:extensionElements>
        <spiffworkflow:preScript>
# ---- PreScript Demo (Task 2) ----
print("PreScript: Order ready for final confirmation")
confirmation_timestamp = get_current_timestamp()
        </spiffworkflow:preScript>
        <spiffworkflow:formLoadScript>
# ---- FormLoadScript Demo (Task 2) ----
view_count = view_count + 1
last_viewed = get_current_timestamp()
print(f"FormLoadScript: Confirmation task viewed {view_count} time(s)")
        </spiffworkflow:formLoadScript>
        <spiffworkflow:instructionsForEndUser>
## Confirm Submission

You are about to submit the following order:

- **Customer:** {{ customer_name }}
- **Total:** {{ formatted_total }}
- **Priority:** {{ priority }}
- **Confirmation prepared at:** {{ confirmation_timestamp }}

---

### Features demonstrated in this workflow:

1. **Code Module** (`helpers.py`): `calculate_order_total()`, `format_currency()`, `get_priority()`, `get_current_timestamp()` — all defined in the process model's Python file and available everywhere.

2. **PreScript**: Ran before each manual task to prepare display data (e.g., `formatted_total`). Check the console panel to see the print output.

3. **FormLoadScript**: The view counter above increments each time you load this page. Navigate away and back to see it change.

4. **Console Output**: Open the console panel to see all `print()` output from scripts, preScripts, and formLoadScripts.

5. **Task Metadata Extraction**: `customer_name`, `priority`, and `order_total` are extracted into task metadata via model-level `task_metadata_extraction_paths` and visible in task list APIs.

6. **Back Button**: Use the Back button to return to the Review Order step. Your view count will persist because formLoadScript runs on reload.

---
*Total page views across both tasks: {{ view_count }}*

*Click Continue to complete the workflow.*
        </spiffworkflow:instructionsForEndUser>
      </bpmn:extensionElements>
      <bpmn:incoming>Flow_3</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>Flow_4</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:manualTask>

    <bpmn:endEvent id="EndEvent_1">
      <bpmn:incoming>Flow_4</bpmn:incoming>
    </bpmn:endEvent>

    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_1" sourceRef="StartEvent_1" targetRef="Activity_InitOrder" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_2" sourceRef="Activity_InitOrder" targetRef="Activity_ReviewOrder" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_3" sourceRef="Activity_ReviewOrder" targetRef="Activity_ConfirmSubmission" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="Flow_4" sourceRef="Activity_ConfirmSubmission" targetRef="EndEvent_1" />

  </bpmn:process>

  <bpmndi:BPMNDiagram id="BPMNDiagram_1">
    <bpmndi:BPMNPlane id="BPMNPlane_1" bpmnElement="Process_feature_showcase">
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="_BPMNShape_StartEvent_2" bpmnElement="StartEvent_1">
        <dc:Bounds x="179" y="159" width="36" height="36" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="Activity_InitOrder_di" bpmnElement="Activity_InitOrder">
        <dc:Bounds x="270" y="137" width="100" height="80" />
        <bpmndi:BPMNLabel />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="Activity_ReviewOrder_di" bpmnElement="Activity_ReviewOrder">
        <dc:Bounds x="430" y="137" width="100" height="80" />
        <bpmndi:BPMNLabel />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="Activity_ConfirmSubmission_di" bpmnElement="Activity_ConfirmSubmission">
        <dc:Bounds x="590" y="137" width="100" height="80" />
        <bpmndi:BPMNLabel />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="EndEvent_1_di" bpmnElement="EndEvent_1">
        <dc:Bounds x="752" y="159" width="36" height="36" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNEdge id="Flow_1_di" bpmnElement="Flow_1">
        <di:waypoint x="215" y="177" />
        <di:waypoint x="270" y="177" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNEdge>
      <bpmndi:BPMNEdge id="Flow_2_di" bpmnElement="Flow_2">
        <di:waypoint x="370" y="177" />
        <di:waypoint x="430" y="177" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNEdge>
      <bpmndi:BPMNEdge id="Flow_3_di" bpmnElement="Flow_3">
        <di:waypoint x="530" y="177" />
        <di:waypoint x="590" y="177" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNEdge>
      <bpmndi:BPMNEdge id="Flow_4_di" bpmnElement="Flow_4">
        <di:waypoint x="690" y="177" />
        <di:waypoint x="752" y="177" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNEdge>
    </bpmndi:BPMNPlane>
  </bpmndi:BPMNDiagram>
</bpmn:definitions>
